  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<h2>Pre-Construction Stage</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assists in preparing the key commercial control documents such as the Procurement Schedule, Cashflow Forecast and Margin Improvement Strategy to ensure the project is well planned.</li>\n  <li>Sending enquires to the market for the assigned packages</li>\n  <li>Analysing subcontractor and supplier tender returns.</li>\n  <li>Flag any risks such as discrepancies in the tender documents to the lead estimator.</li>\n  <li>Prepare/compare material quantity take offs and bills of quantities according to the specifications &amp; drawings submitted by the client.</li>\n  <li>Work with estimating team as required.</li>\n  <li>Gain understanding of commercial strategy for the project, set by Commercial Director.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Post-Contract</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist in change management, inclusive of the valuation of variations, quoting Request for Proposal (RFP)’s, issuing the respective notices, up and downstream, all within the timelines of the main contract.</li>\n  <li>Assist commercial lead in all required commercial monthly reporting both internally and to the client.</li>\n  <li>Always look to improve margin and suggest ways to do so to project lead and assist in techniques employed.</li>\n  <li>Assist in administering the Main Contract, ensuring contract terms are understood and dealt with accordingly.</li>\n  <li>Assist in maintaining project margin in line with commercial strategy.</li>\n  <li>Assist in the preparation of the external valuation,</li>\n  <li>Assist in maintaining control of project documents including drawings and records.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Completion &amp; Post Completion</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist in the agreement of the final account with clients and trade contractors within stipulated benchmark and timelines.</li>\n  <li>Assist in ensuring project is closed out including applying for certificate of release of retention, upon making good defects by Construction Department.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirement</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prefer Singaporean, PR &amp; Malaysian</li>\n</ul>",
